data.enText: a wall or screen that separates one part of a room from another
the division of one country into two or more countries
the partition of Germany after the war

data.chText: 这间屋子被隔为三小间。
data.enText: The room is partitioned into three sections.
to separate one area, one part of a room, etc. from another with a wall or screen

simple_means.memory_skill: part 部分；分开 + ition 行为 → 分成各个部分 → 划分

data.enText: to separate one area, one part of a room, etc. from another with a wall or screen

tr: the act of dividing or partitioning
separation by the creation of a boundary that divides or keeps apart
a vertical structure that divides or separates (as a wall divides one room from another)
(anatomy) a structure that separates areas in an organism
(computer science) the part of a hard disk that is dedicated to a particular operating system or application and accessed as a single unit
divide into parts, pieces, or sections
example: The Arab peninsula was partitioned by the British

value.def: A partition is a wall or screen that separates one part of a room or vehicle from another.

example.ex: ...new offices divided only by glass partitions...
example.tran: 只用玻璃隔板隔开的新办公室

example.ex: Her taxicab has a thick perspex partition between the passengers' seats and the driver.
example.tran: 她的出租车里乘客座位和驾驶员之间装着厚厚的有机玻璃隔板。

value.def: If you partition a room, you separate one part of it from another by means of a partition.

example.ex: Bedrooms have again been created by partitioning a single larger room...
example.tran: 通过将一间大屋用隔断断开的方法再隔出了几间卧室。

example.ex: He sat on the two-seater sofa in the partitioned office.
example.tran: 他坐在用隔板隔开的办公室里的双人沙发上。

value.def: If a country is partitioned, it is divided into two or more independent countries.

example.ex: ...for the first time since Ireland was partitioned...
example.tran: 自爱尔兰被分裂后第一次

example.ex: Britain was accused of trying to partition the country 'because of historic enmity'...
example.tran: 英国被指“出于历史仇恨”企图分裂该国。

example.ex: The island has been partitioned since the mid-seventies.
example.tran: 自从70年代中期以来，这个岛就分裂了。

example.ex: ...areas ruled by the Russian Tsar during Poland's period of partition.
example.tran: 波兰被分割期间俄国沙皇的统治区

example.ex: ...fighting which followed the partition of India.
example.tran: 印度分裂后随之而来的战乱
